\chapter{Running Tutorials}
\label{tutorial-run}

The runner is where the earlier pieces become a usable tool.  It must
decide whether a command resumes an unfinished tutorial or starts a new
run, it must validate each step after the shell exits, and it must make
the saved transcripts easy to review later.

We keep the policy intentionally narrow for v1:
\begin{description}
\item[Resume] the latest unfinished run by default.
\item[Restart] create a fresh run only when the caller asks for it.
\item[Advance] only when the current step passed validation.
\item[Trust] tutorial-authored shell checks only when the caller opts in.
\end{description}


