\section{Performing one step interaction}

The step model only carries one interaction switch: if [[edit_file]] is
set, the runner opens that file in an editor.  Otherwise it falls back to
the existing shell session.

Using a small dispatch helper keeps the main run loop focused on resume
and persistence policy rather than on backend selection.

<<functions>>=
def perform_step(
    step: TutorialStep,
    *,
    workspace: str | Path,
    shell_runner: Callable[..., ShellResult],
    editor_runner: Callable[..., EditorResult],
) -> ShellResult | EditorResult:
    """Run one tutorial step with the appropriate interaction backend."""

    if step.edit_file is not None:
        return editor_runner(
            workspace=workspace,
            relative_path=step.edit_file,
        )
    return shell_runner(workspace=workspace)
@

