\section{Validating one step}

Validation combines recorded-text checks and shell-state checks.
Neither mechanism is enough on its own for the first release, but the two
small checks together cover the common tutorial patterns well.

Shell-state checks need one more guard because they come from tutorial
files.  The runner therefore requires an explicit opt-in before it will
execute tutorial-authored shell commands.

<<functions>>=
def validate_step(
    step: TutorialStep,
    recorded: str,
    workspace: str | Path,
    *,
    allow_shell_checks: bool = False,
) -> bool:
    """Return whether ``step`` passed in ``workspace``."""

    patterns_ok = transcript_matches_patterns(recorded, step.required_patterns)
    command_ok = check_command_passes(
        step.check_command,
        workspace,
        allow_shell_checks=allow_shell_checks,
    )
    return patterns_ok and command_ok
@

<<test functions>>=
def test_validate_step_requires_both_transcript_and_file_state(tmp_path):
    step = TutorialStep(
        title="Create note",
        instructions="Do it.",
        required_patterns=("cat notes.txt",),
        check_command="test -f notes.txt",
    )
